rComments: Work hard and you'll do great. He gives excellent feedback and makes lectures very interesting and always fun to attend.
Excellent lecturer. Boils down complex concepts into clear, step-by-step explanations. Don't self-study for this course: come to class!!

His lectures are clear and well structured. His exams can be quite difficult, but only because they test extensive tracts of material. To do well in 227, do ALL the assigned textbook questions (they often appear on the exams) and memorize the handful of proofs he goes over in class. Good course, difficult, but not as impossible as I feared

Before the first test my friend and I went to his OH. He told us to study the textbook last and focus on the proofs. The test was pretty much all the questions (some assigned some not) from the textbook. Can I prove it in a court of law? No. I did badly and the average was high. If you are to take this class do every question in the textbook.

In Eco475, you will be exposed to graduate-level econometrics, along with papers to read, which will appear on the tests; plus a research paper, and by that I mean a REAL paper (not the first-year 5-page "paper").   Ismael is great; he's fun and chill. Therefore, make sure you 1) Memorize everything 2) Find a good teammate for paper and 3) enjoy
